</ref>

== Foreign honours controversy ==
=== House Resolution 407 ===
On May 19, 2006, [[Mike Fitzpatrick|Michael Fitzpatrick]] ([[United States Republican Party|R]]-[[Pennsylvania|PA]]) introduced a [[concurrent resolution]] designated [[United States House of Representatives|House of Representatives]] Resolution 407<ref>{{cite web
  | last =
  | first =
  | authorlink =
  | coauthors =
  | title =HR 407, [[109th US Congress]]
  | work =
  | publisher =GovTrack.us
  | date =
  | url =http://www.govtrack.us/congress/bill.xpd?bill=hc109-407
  | format =
  | doi =
  | accessdate =  }}
</ref>, and on June 15, 2006, [[Rick Santorum|Richard Santorum]] ([[United States Republican Party|R]]-[[Pennsylvania|PA]]) introduced the identical [[United States Senate|Senate]] Resolution 102<ref>{{cite web
  | last =
  | first =
  | authorlink =
  | coauthors =
  | title =SR 102, 109th US Congress 
  | work =
  | publisher =GovTrack.us
  | date =
  | url =http://www.govtrack.us/congress/bill.xpd?bill=sc109-102
  | format =
  | doi =
  | accessdate =  }}
</ref>, being :
{{Quotation|That [[US Congress|Congress]],<br /> 
* condemn the murder of Philadelphia Police Officer Danny Faulkner
* urge the city of [[Saint-Denis]] to change the name of Rue Mumia Abu-Jamal, and, if they do not, urge the [[Government of France|French government]] to take action against the [[city]] to change the name
* commend police officers all over the world for their commitment to [[public service]] and [[public safety]].|Operative text of proposed HR407, [[109th US Congress]]|May 19, 2006}}

On December 6, 2006, the House of Representatives voted 368-31 in favor of HR407, "Condemning the decision of St. Denis, [[France]], to name a street in honor of Mumia Abu-Jamal, the convicted murderer of Philadelphia Police Officer Danny Faulkner."<ref>{{cite web
  | last =
  | first =
  | authorlink =
