  | work =
  | publisher =US House of Representatives
  | date =December 6, 2006
  | url =http://clerk.house.gov/evs/2006/roll527.xml 
  | format =
  | doi =
  | accessdate =  }}
</ref>

=== Lawsuits involving French municipalities ===
[[Image:Bertrand Delanoe ABr112901.jpeg|thumb|left|110px|[[Bertrand Delanoë]], [[Mayor of Paris]] (2001 - ) and a proponent responsible for conferring honorary Parisian citizenship upon Mumia Abu-Jamal in October 2003]]On December 11, 2006, the executive committee of the [[Republican State Committee of Pennsylvania|Republican Party]] for the 59th Ward of the City of Philadelphia (covering approximately [[Germantown, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania|Germantown, Philadelphia]]), [[lawsuit|filed suit]] with two [http://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plainte plaintes] (criminal complaints on behalf of victims) in forums of the [[French legal system]] against [[Paris#Administration|the government of the city of Paris]] and the city of [[Saint-Denis]] citing the wrong of those cities' actions "glorifying" Mumia Abu-Jamal.<ref>{{cite press release
  | title =59th Republican Ward Executive Committee Files Criminal Charges Against Cities of Paris and Suburb for 'Glorifying' Infamous Philadelphia Cop-Killer
  | publisher =59th Republican Ward Executive Committee - City of Philadelphia
  | date =December 11, 2006
  | url =http://www.politicspa.com/pressreleasedetailed.asp?id=7501
  | accessdate =  }}</ref>

== "Free Mumia" campaign ==
[[Image:MumiaSpanish.jpg|200px|right|thumbnail|[[Barcelona]] street [[propaganda]] calling for the release of Mumia Abu-Jamal]]
{{detail|Free Mumia campaign|the movement to free Mumia Abu-Jamal and its opponents}} 
A broad international movement has allied in support of Mumia Abu-Jamal's cause with noteworthy opposition coalesced about the family of Daniel Faulkner, the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania, and the Fraternal Order of Police.

Whether to protest at perceived injustice affecting him or to deplore the possibility of future application of the death penalty in his and other cases, support encompasses that to date supplied by prominent American [[labor unions]] and congresses<ref>{{cite press release
  | title =San Francisco [[ILWU]] Local 10 Executive Board Resolution - Support for April 24, 1999 demonstrations in favour of the cause of Mumia Abu-Jamal (also describing support of other named labour union groups)
